The paper deals with multiplayer games and their Nash equilibria, which are topics commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on distributed and embedded systems suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of simple strategies and the promise of implementability suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
